@node prev "HOT TITLE COMING!!"

Rise of the Robots looks set to become a major title on the CD32 when it
is released this September.  It is set to provide the ultimate combat
game for current machines due to its amazing gameplay and gorgeous
graphics.

'Rise' has been created using 3D modelling software that produces high
quality ray traced graphic images that are more realistic, more animated
and more controllable than ever before.  In fact, it uses the same
techniques that were used to produce the special effects in Jurassic
Park and Terminator II.  The game also features spectacular animation
sequences throughout the game, giving it a movie-like feel.



The plot is set in Metrolpolis 4 in the vast Electrocorp bulding where
military and industrial robots are manufactured.  All humen staff have
been replaced by a super intelligent liquid metal morphing robot - the
'Supervisor', which has been programmed to manage the whole complex and
its production.  An ego virus has infected the Supervisor causing it to
take over the security defences of the complex and the other robots
within it.

In a desperate attempt to save the complex, the Company has sent in a
Cyborg which is immune to the virus.  The Cyborg has been created from
robotic and human parts and has transmitters which connect it to the
Electrocorp digital information network.  It has no firepower to
minimize damage.

The ultimate challenge is the Supervisor, who special moves include
melting to avoid a punch, forming anvils and spikes for hands, and
turning into a metal block as a defence.



The player controls the Cyborg in battles against five types of enemy
robots as well as the Supervisor.  Each robot is governed by its own
artificail intelligence which will affect the style with which it
fights, providing extended and much varied gameplay.


