@node blac "BLACK RAIN"

Stars    : Michael Douglas, Andy Garcia and lots of Japanese actors..
Director : Ridley Scott
Cert.    : 18
Length   : 125 Mins


        Now, anyone who know's anything about Ridley Scott, director of
The Aliens Trilogy and Blade Runner, will go into this film expecting 
great things.  Unfortunately, Black Rain just does not live up to Ridley 
Scott's name, and is certainly not a film that you would want to watch 
more than a few times.

        Douglas plays a New York Cop who strongarms his way through the
Japanese underworld in pursuit of the maverick gangster who killed his 
buddy.  The film contains lot's of killing, which is reflected by the
fact that it is the only FMV title at the moment to have an 18 rating.

The tried and tested method of a cop seeking revenge combined with Scott's
very dark style of film-making should have produced a sure fire hit, but
it seems to fall at the first hurdle.  It is doubtful that you will 
watch this more than a couple of times other than to freeze-frame the
shot where Andy Garcia is decapitated by a Samurai Sword.


CD32Bits Rating - **
@endnode
@node ghos "GHOST"

Stars    : Patrick Swayze, Demi Moore and Whoopi Goldberg
Director : Jerry Zucker
Cert     : 15
Length   : 121 Mins


        This is by far the best title available on Video CD at the 
present time.  It is in White Book format, so the quality of the 
production is seamless, with perfect sound and no jumping.  Well done 
Paramount.  The only problem that I could find was that the film only 
comes in Wide Screen, which means that you have two black bands above
and below the main picture, although the film is so enjoyable that you 
soon forget that the bars are there.

        It's a wraith against time as the restless spirit of a murdered 
man (Swayze) tries desperately to warn the love of his former life 
(Moore) that the hoodlum who killed him is out ot get her too.  He finds
a charlatan psychic (Goldberg) who is amazed to find that her powers are
for real and eventually agrees to help him.  Ghost is a love story, a 
thriler and a comedy all thrown into one, and a serious tear jerker!!

        Definately one for the ladies, and probably one for the men too!
                                BUY IT NOW!!


CD32Bits Rating - *****
@endnode
@node hunt "The Hunt For Red October"

Stars    : Sean Connery, Alec Baldwin and Sam Neill
Director : John McTiernen
Cert     : PG
Length   : 137 Mins


        From the director of Die Hard comes The Hunt For Red October, 
the tale of a Russian Navy Commander trying to defect to the US.

        It isn't only the Americans who see red when a Soviet super-sub 
skipper skips, and heads his hi-tech craft straight for them.  The 
Russians do, too.  For neither side is really sure whether the Ruskie 
runaway is a renegade who wants to start a war, or a defector who wants 
to stop one.

        There's not much on the action front in this movie and it is
doubtful that you will want to watch it much more than a couple of
times. Whilst maintaining a tense atmosphere throughout, it fails to 
pack a punch like McTiernens other smash hit, Die Hard.  Story by the 
Author of Patriot Games.


